⏪ Recap – an AI newsletter of everything you've saved recently

ratio ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4QXJM27A_JM )We all save content, articles and make notes to look at later... except… we never come back to it.

 

Useful ideas get lost and forgotten – they're saved somewhere, but we don't remember to look at them, and never benefit from them.

 

What if we actually read the stuff that we saved to read later?

 

 ⏪ Recap solves this.

 

Get your "read it later" content regularly sent to your email at a time of your choosing, when you'll actually read it.

With a convenient AI summary for each file, note or link, helping you reflect and review.

 

Try out Recap today (on any paid plan) ( https://fabric.so/ )
  

🌗 Dark mode

You've been asking us for this for a long time – but it's now here. Enjoy Fabric in a new dark mode, making it gentler on your eyes for long periods of use. We hope you enjoy it :)

Try Fabric in dark mode ( https://fabric.so/ )
  

Other improvements

- We've added the ability to create a title when making a quick note, so that annoyance is gone (not sure why didn't add that earlier, in hindsight...)

- Improved Assistant responses for images and saved bookmarks, with better analysis of the content

- A nicer mobile UI for viewing an item, or swiping between them (a lot more coming here soon)

- Added alphabetical sorting, and a new sorting UI

- We've rewritten a ton of the app to improve the speed of loading, content refreshing, and navigation. Fabric is now much lighter on your phone or laptop, reducing CPU usage and battery drain.

Much more coming here – it's a big focus for us.

  

 

